-- Samsung Offers Slovak Research Center to Win State Aid, HN Says
-- B y   R a d o s l a v   T o m e k
-- 2012-03-08T07:56:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-08/samsung-offers-slovak-research-center-to-win-state-aid-hn-says.html
Samsung Electronics Co. (005930)  pledged to
set up a research center in Slovakia to win state aid for the
expansion of a factory in the east European country,  Hospodarske
Noviny  reported, citing premier  Iveta Radicova .  The South Korean company is asking the government for state
aid worth 28 million euros ($37 million) in exchange for
investing 90 million euros into its existing factory in Galanta,
western Slovakia. The government will discuss the request after
the March 10 elections, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Radoslav Tomek in Bratislava at 
 rtomek@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
